X:1
T:Ornament Drill — GHP chanter
C:Tony Koop / sheet-music skill (warmup)
M:4/4
L:1/8
Q:1/4=60
K:Amix
H:Pipe-band ornament practice. Each line drills one ornament family;
H:repeat each line eight times before moving on. The drill is *slow*
H:on purpose — speed comes after the ornament cluster is clean.
H:NO RESTS — held principal notes between clusters.
% --- Doubling on low A: {GdG}A2  ---
{GdG}A2 {GdG}A2 {GdG}A2 {GdG}A2 |
% --- Doubling on B: {GdG}B2  ---
{GdG}B2 {GdG}B2 {GdG}B2 {GdG}B2 |
% --- Doubling on C# (c in K:Amix): {GdG}c2 ---
{GdG}c2 {GdG}c2 {GdG}c2 {GdG}c2 |
% --- Doubling on D: {GeG}d2 ---
{GeG}d2 {GeG}d2 {GeG}d2 {GeG}d2 |
% --- Doubling on E: {ge}e2 ---
{ge}e2 {ge}e2 {ge}e2 {ge}e2 |
% --- Doubling on F#: {gf}f2 ---
{gf}f2 {gf}f2 {gf}f2 {gf}f2 |
% --- Doubling on high A: {gag}a2 ---
{gag}a2 {gag}a2 {gag}a2 {gag}a2 |
% --- Throw on D from low A: {GdGcd}d (compound grace cluster) ---
A2 {GdGcd}d2 A2 {GdGcd}d2 |
% --- Birl: {GAGA}A2 — repeated low-A with G grace between ---
{GAGA}A2 {GAGA}A2 {GAGA}A2 {GAGA}A2 |
% --- Cadence held low A ---
{GBG}A8 |]
